            <scopecontent id="aspace_40488c2d36ae4fbce00b8530764b6bd5">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The papers of Henry Stevens consist of eleven letters concerning books and cataloging, two short writings and a manuscript advertisement by Henry Stevens, and a few other miscellaneous items. The papers were given to Yale University in separate gifts by Henry Stevens (1847), Roland A. L. Tree (1935), and the estate of Andrew Keogh (1953).</p>
